Questions: What is Admission Requirements or acceptance Requirements or approval Requirements or consent Requirements?
Answers: The program receives students who have a high school certificate in scientific department (science - mathematics) according to the organized rules.Students from the Science department must pass the "Math 2" course within the specified period.

Questions: What is Transfer Requirements or convey Requirements or transport Requirements or shift Requirements or Transfer To Future Academy Requirements ?
Answers: The institute allows transfers to the program from students of the equivalent institutes and colleges. Admission requires a scientific equivalency for courses and requires non-transfer in the final year for students with a score of 75% or more.

Questions: What is Requirements for transferring between study programs or convey Requirements between study programs or transport Requirements between study programs or shift Requirementsbetween study programs ?
Answers: The student is allowed to transfer between study programs with a scientific equivalency of courses. Transfer is allowed twice during the period of his study at the Institute with respecting the general rules of transfer.

Questions: what is Specializations and degree or expertise and degree or specialist and degree ?
Answers: The graduate of the program is given a bachelor's degree in the field of computer science. Variety in the licensed specializations of the institute.

Questions: What is Language of study ?
Answers: The language of study in the program is English or Arabic. The exam must be in the same language as instruction.

Questions: What is Academic Advisor Role or educational mentor Role or Academic mentor Role or educational  Advisor Role ?
Answers: The Institute assigns each student an academic advisor to assist him in his academic choices. It is preferable for the advisor to stay with the student until his graduation.

Questions: What is Studying courses online or Studying track online ?
Answers: Some courses are allowed to be taught online in specific conditions.The final exam is held within the institute and follows the organizing instructions.

Questions: What is List of courses and students that enroll in those courses or List of courses and students that register in those courses or List of courses and students that enrollment in those courses ?
Answers: Before the beginning of any semester, the Institute announces the list of courses and opens the door for registration. ? The Board of Directors of the Institute determines the minimum and maximum number of students in each course according to the capabilities of the Institute. The student enrolls in the courses of his choice in coordination with the academic advisor as long as they are available.

Questions: How Can Deleting and adding courses or remove and build on course or  take off and include courses ?
Answers: The student can delete or add courses after completing the registration procedures. This is allowed within two weeks of the beginning of the study without academic or financial commitments.

Questions: What is Suspension of student enrollment or adjournment of student enrollmen or postponement of student enrollment ?
Answers: The Institute's Board of Directors has the right to suspend a student's enrollment for one or more semesters (up to a maximum of 4 semesters) in the case of an acceptable excuse. A student who does not attend registration within the first two weeks of the semester, does not apply for enrollment suspension, and does not provide an acceptable excuse approved by the Institute's Board of Directors, is deprived of registration for that semester and receives an "Academic Warning.

Questions: What The Letter of my GPA ?
How can Calculation of Course Points ?
Answers: course points for a student are obtained by multiplying the credit hours of the Course by the numeric grade achieved by the student

Questions: how can Calculation of Semester GPA ?
Answers: Semester GPA is calculated by dividing the total Course points the student earned in the Semester by the total credit hours of those courses.

Questions: how can cumulative GPA or accumulative GPA?
Answers: Cumulative GPA is calculated by dividing the total course points the student earned up to the current date by the total credit hours of those courses.

Questions: what is Course Registration or Course recording or Course enrollment ?
Answers: The maximum credit hours a student can register for each semester are nine (9) hours. Exceeding this limit requires approval from the Institute's Board of Directors in exceptional cases, such as graduation

Questions: what is Maximum Approved Credit Hours or  Maximum confirmed Credit Hours?
Answers: Linked to the cumulative GPA: Cumulative GPA 3 or above: 21 hours. Cumulative GPA 2 - less than 3: 18 hours. Cumulative GPA 1 - less than 2: 15 hours. Cumulative GPA less than 1: 12 hours. New program entrants: 21 hours in the first semester

Questions: what is  the summer semester?
Answers: Cumulative GPA 3 or above: 9 hours. Cumulative GPA less than 3: 6 hours.

Questions: how can make Course Withdrawal?
Answers: A student may withdraw from a course or more until the end of the seventh week from the start of the semester, provided that the student's registered credit hours do not fall below the minimum registration requirement (Article 13). In this case, the student's status in the records is "W," indicating withdrawal, without affecting the cumulative GPA.

Questions: what is the Types of Program Courses or category of Program Courses?
Answers: Compulsory (mandatory) or (elective). ? A course may be either compulsory or elective. A prerequisite course must be passed before registering for another course. The prerequisite must be a mandatory course within the same program, and its code must be lower than the code of the course.

Questions: what is the Exceeding Basic Credit Hours or exceptional Basic Credit Hours?
Answers: The Institute's Board of Directors, with the approval of the department council and program director, may allow a student to exceed the requirement of passing the prerequisite course to register for another course. The student must not register for the prerequisite and its requirement in the same semester, except in exceptional circumstances, such as graduation. A student who fails in any course can study the course and its prerequisite in the same semester.

Questions: what is the Exam Attendance Disqualification or Exam Attendance dismissal or Exam Attendance expulsion?
Answers: If a student is absent from the final exam, they are considered to have failed the course. If the student provides a valid excuse within two days (excluding the exam day), accepted bthe Institute's Board, their status in the records becomes "Incomplete (I)" for that course without affecting their cumulative GPA. A student who has attended at least 75% of lectures and exercises for the course and is disqualified from taking the final exam is considered to have failed. In this case, the student is considered failed unless they provide an acceptable excuse, approved by the Institute's Board, and their status in the records becomes "Incomplete (I)" for that course without affecting their cumulative GPA.

Questions: How Can Repeating the Same Course Multiple Times , How Improve The GPA ?
Answers: If the repetition is a result of failure, the student is granted the grade they obtained in the last repetition, not exceeding the maximum grade of B+ in the first repetition, C+ in the second repetition, and D+ in any subsequent repetition. If the repetition is for the purpose of improvement, the student is given the grade they obtained in the last repetition as is. If that grade falls into the "Fail (F)" category and the student repeats it in the second repetition, the above item is applicable.

Questions: When I Get Academic warnings and dismissal or Academic warnings and disconnect ?
Answers: The student receives an academic warning when his GPA drops below 2.0, and is dismissed if he receives 4 consecutive warnings or 6 sperated warnings. In case of dismissal for any reason and with a progress rate of 80% of the hours required for graduation, he is given a last chance for two semesters if the student does not meet the graduation requirements, he will be permanently dismissed from the institute.

Questions: What Is Summer Training Rolls ?
Answers: After completing 30 credit hours, each student undertakes a summer training (internal or external) after 120 hours distributed over four weeks at least , and the examination board determines the student's status as "passed" or "did not pass" or assigned him a compensatory project.

Questions: What Is Rolls Of Graduation Project ?
Answers: At the end of his/her studies, the student submits a graduation project after completing 70% of the required hours. The project is enrolled as two consecutive courses, and it is implemented no less than 4 weeks after the end of the exams.

Questions: What is Requirements for obtaining a bachelor's degree or Requirements for gain a bachelor's degree or Requirements for achieve a bachelor's degree or Requirements for acquire a bachelor's degree ?
Answers:
The student is given the bachelor's degree after completion of 134 credit hours. There are two requirements : First requirement: GPA is not less than 2.0 
Second requirement : not to violate rule No. (14) throughout the duration of the study. Not completing one of the two requirements will result in the student not obtaining the grade.

Questions: what is  Non-humanities courses ?
Answers: All non-humanities courses consist of 3 credit hours (two hours for lectures and two hours for practical or exercises).

Questions: what is  Humanities courses ?
Answers: All humanities courses consist of 2 credit hours (two hours for lectures).

Questions: what is  Exam time?
Answers: The exam time for all courses is two hours.

Questions: what is  The final grade of Courses
Answers: The final grade of all courses is 100 marks (60 for the final exam and 40 for semester work).

Questions: What is the study system and course distribution for the Computer Science Department?
Answers: Study at the Academy is based on the credit hour system, The academic year is divided into two semesters in addition to a summer semester,The credit hour is the measure of every academic subject

Questions: What are the requirements To obtain a bachelor's degree in computer science? or what are  Requirements for gain a bachelor's degree ? or what are Requirements for achieve a bachelor's degree ? or what are Requirements for acquire a bachelor's degree ?
Answers:
The student must successfully pass 134 (one hundred and thirty-four) credit hours. The hundred and thirty-four hours are divided between Mandatory or elective requirements, whether university or major. 
 
Courses 
To obtain a bachelor's degree in computer science, 134 Credit hours studies are required distributed as follows 
A- General requirements (14) credit hours:   (6) Mandatory credit hours  (8)Credit Hours chosen by the student from among the elective courses  
B- Department requirements (63) credit hours: It is divided into two parts 
 Mathematics and basic sciences (statistics and physics and electronics) (24) Mandatory credit hours. Basic Computer Science (39) Mandatory credit hours.
C- Major requirements (57) credit hours: 
Applied Sciences (39) Mandatory credit hours )12( Credit hours chosen by the student from among the elective courses in the same major, or he can choose a maximum of 6 hours from Mandatory or elective courses from any other major. 
 (6) Credit hours Graduation Project

Questions: What is Code system rules for courses ?

A-The code for any course consists of the code for the department or specialization major to which the course belongs, followed by a three-digit number Its details are as follows:

 B- The code system for the department or major: • Computer Science code = CSC  • BSC Mathematics and basic sciences such as statistics, physics, etc.,  • Humanities
